<TITLE> 10 die as bus, truck collide in Comilla </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Comilla, Nov 6 (bdnews24.com) - Ten people were killed when a truck and a bus collided head-on on Dhaka-Chittagong highway near Korpai under Burichong Upazila of Comilla on Thursday, police said. Containers of acid turned upside down from the truck and fell on the right side of the bus, which caught fire and was burned. The blaze burned ten passengers of the bus to death and injured at least 30 others, Burichong police officer-in-charge Anwar Hossain said. Ten people who were critically injured were admitted to Comilla Combined Military Hospital (CMH) and other hospitals. The rest were given first aid. The identities of those killed and injured could not be immediately known. Hossain said a passenger bus of Unique Paribahan coming from Dhaka to Chittagong collided head-on with the oncoming truck in Korpai around 3:20pm. On information fire fighters from Comilla rushed to the spot and managed to douse the fire in one hour, Hossain added. Traffic on the highway remained stopped for about one hour after the incident. Later police went to the spot and brought the situation under control at around 4:30pm. The police official said Comilla deputy commissioner Md Monzurur Rahman and additional superintendent of police Md Shamsuzzoha visited the spot. Hossain said a committee headed by Comilla additional district magistrate Nazmul Haque Khan had been formed to investigate the accident. bdnews
